WEBVTT

00:03.253 --> 00:05.021
Cal hartley,
eccentric gazillionaire--

00:05.088 --> 00:07.123
And my future sugar daddy--
mwah!--

00:07.174 --> 00:09.124
Saved the company from famine

00:09.176 --> 00:11.544
With a generous infusion
of cash.

00:11.611 --> 00:14.346
Yes, the seemingly preposterous
rumors are true--

00:14.414 --> 00:17.116
People are actually eating
at "mode."

00:17.184 --> 00:18.584
Yikes.

00:18.652 --> 00:21.353
(mouth full)
what? i like doughnuts.

00:25.507 --> 00:27.125
Mmm... chocolate.

00:27.209 --> 00:29.277
(hilda) ugh. please don't
be one of those

00:29.328 --> 00:31.796
"kiss with food in the mouth"
couples. that's just gross.

00:31.880 --> 00:34.582
It's such a relief that things
are finally better at meade.

00:34.633 --> 00:36.934
(betty) also, today is
our annual performance review.

00:37.019 --> 00:39.454
And i think i'm gonna ask
for a promotion...

00:39.521 --> 00:40.938
To editor.

00:41.023 --> 00:42.757
(gasps)
all right!

00:42.824 --> 00:44.826
Bravo, mija. bravo!
plus, you still have
your y.e.t.i. final project,

00:44.893 --> 00:48.146
So you'll get some
job interviews from that, too.
so will you.

00:48.230 --> 00:51.532
I know, but we were
talking about you.
wait. you're not leaving
"mode," are you?

00:51.583 --> 00:54.052
Because that's the only reason
why popular girls invite me

00:54.136 --> 00:56.854
To get manicures with them.
i'm not leaving.

00:56.939 --> 00:58.506
It's just good
to have options.

00:58.573 --> 01:01.592
I mean, she's like
manny ramirez last winter.

01:01.660 --> 01:04.278
Yeah, i don't know
what that means.

01:04.346 --> 01:06.781
A free agent? you know,
she can leverage offers

01:06.832 --> 01:08.966
Against each other,
try to get the best--

01:09.051 --> 01:11.602
Yeah, i should really
know my audience.
welcome to my world.

01:11.687 --> 01:13.654
Thanks, ignacio.
(chuckles)

01:19.311 --> 01:21.446
Oops.

01:23.000 --> 01:29.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:33.375 --> 01:34.959
Good morning, boss.

01:35.043 --> 01:37.278
I'm here
for my performance review.

01:37.329 --> 01:38.763
Good morning.

01:38.847 --> 01:40.248
Right on time, employee,

01:40.299 --> 01:44.819
Which leads nicely into...
punctuality--excellent.

01:44.886 --> 01:46.954
Attitude--excellent.

01:47.022 --> 01:50.541
It kills me to say this,
but across the board,

01:50.626 --> 01:52.994
You... are adequate.

01:53.061 --> 01:55.780
(sighs) oh, willie!

01:55.864 --> 01:58.132
You have never said that
to me before.

01:58.183 --> 02:00.518
I want to hug you.
dial it back, sister,

02:00.586 --> 02:03.121
Or i'll drop you
right back down to "subpar."
of course.

02:03.205 --> 02:06.591
Excellent. initiative--
oh, speaking of,
i booked you ten tans

02:06.675 --> 02:09.310
To get ready
for the summer.

02:09.377 --> 02:11.979
We don't want the "post"
calling you pasty again.
oh. when did they
call me pasty?

02:12.030 --> 02:13.464
Oh, last june.

02:13.549 --> 02:16.067
But you didn't see it
because i threw it away.

02:16.151 --> 02:18.119
Oh! another example
of initiative.

02:18.187 --> 02:21.322
I was hoping, in light
of my recent adequacy,

02:21.373 --> 02:24.809
That we might talk
about my... future here.

02:24.877 --> 02:27.361
Well, uh, actually,

02:27.429 --> 02:30.331
There is something
you need to know.

02:30.399 --> 02:33.167
A hiring freeze?
what does that mean?

02:33.235 --> 02:35.686
It was part of the deal
we made with hartley.

02:35.771 --> 02:38.356
We got to hire back
everyone we let go,

02:38.440 --> 02:40.241
But until someone leaves...

02:40.309 --> 02:43.311
(clears throat)
there are no new positions.

02:43.378 --> 02:46.264
And everyone
just got hired back,

02:46.348 --> 02:48.299
So why would they want
to leave?

02:48.383 --> 02:50.635
I'm so sorry, betty.

02:50.719 --> 02:53.237
Look, the thought of losing you
absolutely kills me,

02:53.322 --> 02:55.223
But i know you have
bigger aspirations than...

02:55.290 --> 02:57.191
(scoffs) booking my tans.

02:57.259 --> 03:00.077
But if an opportunity
arises at y.e.t.i.,

03:00.162 --> 03:03.581
No one will sing your praises
louder than i will.

03:19.648 --> 03:21.265
(sighs)

03:36.262 --> 03:39.264
Thanks so much for helping me
with my hair.

03:39.332 --> 03:42.518
I'm meeting your father later,
and i want to look good.

03:42.602 --> 03:45.287
Why? so he can feel worse
when you break his heart?

03:45.372 --> 03:47.556
I found this.

03:47.624 --> 03:50.359
What are you doing
going through my mail?

03:50.427 --> 03:53.345
What are you doing looking
for "nurse educator" positions

03:53.396 --> 03:54.847
In chula vista--

03:54.914 --> 03:56.815
A country
i've never even heard of?!

03:56.866 --> 03:58.917
Chula vista's
in california.

03:58.968 --> 04:01.203
And i wasn't looking
for anything.

04:01.287 --> 04:03.288
I just took
an informational meeting

04:03.340 --> 04:05.240
When i was visiting family.
(paper rustles)

04:05.325 --> 04:07.493
I never thought anythi
would come of it.

04:07.544 --> 04:11.280
So you're just gonna, what,
you're just gonna leave?
no.

04:11.348 --> 04:14.366
Ay! come on, i don't know.

04:14.417 --> 04:16.769
It's a really good job.

04:16.836 --> 04:19.704
It'd be a new challenge,
a raise.

04:19.773 --> 04:23.625
Ignacio's
a really great guy.

04:23.710 --> 04:26.095
Well, you gotta tell him
what's going on.

04:26.179 --> 04:27.963
He deserves to know.

04:28.031 --> 04:29.915
You're right.

04:29.966 --> 04:32.634
Plus, i have
a really big mouth.

04:32.719 --> 04:34.620
So if you don't tell him,

04:34.671 --> 04:37.389
He might
just find out, anyway.
(sighs)

04:37.457 --> 04:39.858
(wilhelmina) okay, let's run
through the bridal issue

04:39.926 --> 04:41.343
One last time.

04:41.428 --> 04:43.762
If anyone has any notes,
i don't care.

04:43.813 --> 04:46.098
Oh, cal,
what are you doing back?

04:46.166 --> 04:48.667
I thought
you were in siberia.
oh, they had
a damn earthquake.

04:48.718 --> 04:51.320
As soon as they clear
the bodies, i'll be back.

04:51.404 --> 04:53.405
Well, if you need
any work space,

04:53.456 --> 04:57.743
Marc will set you up.
actually, i'd rather see
what you're doing here.

04:57.810 --> 04:59.561
No pressure.

04:59.646 --> 05:02.648
Hmm.
just looking for something
to make me smile.

05:02.716 --> 05:04.249
I'm not smiling.

05:04.317 --> 05:06.718
Now i'm not saying

05:06.770 --> 05:09.238
That you have to change
your whole concept,

05:09.322 --> 05:13.242
But the wedding dresses
aren't popping.

05:13.326 --> 05:15.494
Now what if we put...
(both mouth words)

05:15.545 --> 05:18.714
The cherry 7up antioxidant ad...

05:18.798 --> 05:22.584
Between these photos?

05:22.669 --> 05:25.687
There. very nice.
breathe. i have pictures of
all of this. we will rebuild.

05:25.772 --> 05:27.256
"cherry pick
your antioxidants."

05:27.340 --> 05:29.541
See? now that's clever.
(chuckles)

05:29.592 --> 05:31.994
Excuse me, where do you
think you're going?

05:32.061 --> 05:35.247
(french accent) uh, i would
like a cherry 7up antioxidant.

05:35.314 --> 05:37.750
Well, in america,
we just say "7up."

05:37.801 --> 05:40.068
But it contains vitamin e,
a powerful antioxidant.

05:40.153 --> 05:43.856
Oh, for god sake, will you talk
like a normal person? sit down.

05:43.907 --> 05:47.309
Yeah, see, my eye still isn't
being drawn to the clothes.

05:46.393 --> 05:49.112
I don't know.
maybe we have to reshoot.

05:49.196 --> 05:51.064
(chuckles) if i may...
what?

05:51.131 --> 05:52.365
Uh, marc?
yes.

05:52.416 --> 05:54.317
It--it's not that simple.

05:54.401 --> 05:56.786
We've been working
on this concept for months.

05:56.871 --> 05:59.506
This is a little
black wedding dress.

05:59.557 --> 06:02.392
My dear friend, reem acra,
designed some things personally,

06:02.476 --> 06:03.927
As a huge favor.

06:04.011 --> 06:06.763
I think it is our best
wedding issue as of yet.

06:06.847 --> 06:10.300
All right, you don't have
to take my ideas.

06:10.384 --> 06:13.820
Of course,
you did takey money.
(claire) are you going
to be much longer?

06:13.887 --> 06:17.557
I booked this conference room
for a "hot flash" meeting.
yes, yes, yes,
your irritable bowel issue.

06:17.608 --> 06:20.360
Yeah, claire, come here.
we need another opinion.

06:20.411 --> 06:24.481
Now tell me, what do you
think of this concept?

06:24.565 --> 06:27.750
I like the idea
of doing something

06:27.818 --> 06:29.719
Other than a white wedding,

06:29.804 --> 06:31.938
But black in fashion
is just as cliché.

06:31.989 --> 06:35.024
In--in europe, they're showing
color in their bridal gowns.

06:35.109 --> 06:38.044
Maybe we could try that.
see, that makes me smile.

06:38.111 --> 06:41.381
You know, maybe you can help
wilhelmina work up some...

06:41.432 --> 06:43.900
New version
of this spread, huh?
what?

06:43.984 --> 06:46.052
I'll clear my calendar.

06:47.605 --> 06:49.589
(gasps)

06:55.643 --> 06:58.612
Oh, there's something i want
to show you on the light board.

06:58.679 --> 07:01.031
I think you'll get
a kick out of it.
okay.

07:01.082 --> 07:03.416
Daniel, hey, since i don't have
a direct supervisor,

07:03.501 --> 07:05.452
I wrote
my own performance review.

07:05.536 --> 07:08.538
I am "super excellent"
in every category.

07:08.606 --> 07:10.223
Would you just sign here?
oh!

07:10.308 --> 07:12.626
Oh, my god.
i can't believe this.

07:12.693 --> 07:15.462
(romantic instrumental music
playing)
yes!

07:15.530 --> 07:17.480
Oh, i love you.

07:17.548 --> 07:19.499
(kisses)
i love you so much.

07:19.567 --> 07:21.968
Wow... it's just paula abdul
yelling at a mailbox.

07:22.053 --> 07:24.938
I was hoping for maybe
a little chuckle or something.

07:25.022 --> 07:28.308
(music warbles and fades)

07:28.392 --> 07:31.394
Oh, no, molly.
you thought i was...

07:31.445 --> 07:33.830
(sighs)
i'm sor--i'm sorry.
no.

07:33.881 --> 07:36.800
It's for
the wedding issue, obviously.

07:36.851 --> 07:39.302
Oh, no. she definitely
thought you were proposing.

07:39.353 --> 07:43.557
Yikes. that is
really embarrassing.

07:43.641 --> 07:47.644
(jodie)
and tom, carson and rita

07:47.711 --> 07:49.746
Are team three.
(laughs)

07:49.797 --> 07:53.617
Three! also the number
of martinis i had last night

07:53.668 --> 07:56.753
After my boyfriend dumped me,
but i digress.

07:56.804 --> 08:01.557
And team four
is marc, betty...

08:01.609 --> 08:03.760
And chair.

08:03.811 --> 08:05.779
Oh. "chair" is matt.

08:05.863 --> 08:07.264
He's not here.
he's coming.

08:07.331 --> 08:09.449
But he's very invested
in all of this.

08:09.533 --> 08:11.635
Uh-huh. they say
they're invested,

08:11.702 --> 08:13.904
And then they go back
to their wife.

08:13.971 --> 08:16.523
Ugh. can i get
a new team?

08:16.591 --> 08:19.092
If you like,
i could be your partner.

08:19.176 --> 08:22.195
Give you a taste of someone
with experience.

08:22.263 --> 08:24.614
Uh, i'm good with betty
and "chair."

08:24.665 --> 08:26.182
(chuckles)

08:26.250 --> 08:28.068
(door opens and closes)

08:28.152 --> 08:30.103
Hey, sorry.

08:30.187 --> 08:32.772
She's assigning final projects.
where were you?

08:32.857 --> 08:35.241
There was this amazing exhibit
at the whitney.

08:35.326 --> 08:37.277
I just lost track of time.

08:37.345 --> 08:39.361
In this bag is the key
to your future.

08:39.413 --> 08:41.831
Your final assignment
is to do a photo shoot

08:41.881 --> 08:43.316
And feature article

08:43.400 --> 08:46.252
For whatever type of magazine
you draw.

08:52.408 --> 08:53.641
"music."

08:53.726 --> 08:56.828
Hey, you didn't
screw it up.
cool!

08:56.895 --> 08:59.381
Draw again.

08:59.465 --> 09:01.349
(paper rustles)

09:01.417 --> 09:03.785
"physical sciences."
ugh.

09:03.836 --> 09:05.487
Which one's our topic?

09:05.554 --> 09:08.490
Both. you didn't think
i'd make this easy, did you?

09:08.557 --> 09:11.642
I like to spice things up.

09:13.429 --> 09:16.914
Now... i have some bad news.

09:16.966 --> 09:20.518
Due to the number
of hiring freezes

09:20.569 --> 09:22.904
In the industry this year,

09:22.988 --> 09:25.790
Y.e.t.i. will only be able
to set up job interviews

09:25.841 --> 09:27.275
For three people.

09:27.359 --> 09:30.928
That means...
only the winning team

09:30.980 --> 09:34.032
Will be getting interviews.
(people groan)

09:34.083 --> 09:36.701
What?
that was our only chance
of moving up.

09:36.752 --> 09:38.153
I'm sorry.

09:38.237 --> 09:40.922
This is just the reality
you have to deal with.

09:41.006 --> 09:42.941
And sometimes reality sucks.

09:42.992 --> 09:46.111
Okay. .

09:46.178 --> 09:48.913
All right, well, then we're
just gonna have to make

09:48.981 --> 09:51.048
The best music/physical science
magazine ever.

09:51.100 --> 09:52.851
Group hug?

09:52.918 --> 09:55.386
Oh.
ooh! aah!

09:58.491 --> 10:01.142
Sync by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com
Thx to YYeTs.net for the transcripts.

10:07.143 --> 10:10.143
Alright, the physical science and music.
Piece of cake.

10:11.460 --> 10:14.179
Easy-squeezy.
okay, but let's start
with the visuals.

10:14.246 --> 10:15.647
Because words--
who cares?

10:15.698 --> 10:17.666
Well, uh, hmm, astronomy
is a physical science.

10:17.750 --> 10:20.185
And there's a jazz club
not too far from here.

10:20.252 --> 10:22.621
We could shoot the musicians
playing, uh, telescopes

10:22.672 --> 10:24.622
Instead of instruments.
okay, yeah,
that's something.

10:24.674 --> 10:27.092
(snores) that's nothing.

10:27.159 --> 10:30.195
We have to do something
amazing, like, eye-popping.

10:30.246 --> 10:33.364
Oh! u2 on a space shuttle.
that definitely doesn't
sound easy-squeezy.

10:33.416 --> 10:35.850
(gasps) oh, my god, you guys
have to come check out

10:35.935 --> 10:37.752
This youtube video.
some lady called 9-1-1

10:37.837 --> 10:41.006
Because they ran out
of chicken nuggets.
ooh, i heard
about that.

10:41.073 --> 10:43.959
Oh, what if we did something
at the planetarium?

10:44.043 --> 10:46.578
Ooh, and maybe use
their laser light show?

10:46.646 --> 10:48.046
But how about,

10:48.113 --> 10:50.348
Instead of pink floyd,
we use somebody current

10:50.399 --> 10:53.335
And then we style them
'70s glam rock?
and--and the article
could be about

10:53.402 --> 10:55.754
How we search to be connected
in this vast universe

10:55.805 --> 10:59.341
And music unites us.
i have no idea what that
means, but it sounded great.

10:59.425 --> 11:02.310
You write it.
great. and i'll also start
working on the logistics.

11:02.395 --> 11:04.329
You know,
booking a photographer,

11:04.380 --> 11:07.732
Getting a caterer,
that sort of stuff.
and i'll get the band.
it's only five degrees

11:07.783 --> 11:09.935
Of gay separation
from anyone good.
(amanda and matt laughing)

11:09.986 --> 11:12.770
I'm worried that
mr. "short attention span"

11:12.822 --> 11:14.623
Over there
isn't focused.

11:14.707 --> 11:16.775
Oh, don't worry.
he heard everything.

11:16.826 --> 11:19.995
Is there something
you'd like to oversee?
sure, sure, i know somebody
at the planetarium.

11:20.062 --> 11:24.015
I can give her a call.
see? all righty,
let's talk specifics.

11:24.083 --> 11:26.084
Okay, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait.

11:26.135 --> 11:29.253
We're about to watch a gopher
make a dramatic face.
(gasps)

11:29.305 --> 11:31.940
(dramatic music plays)

11:32.024 --> 11:33.842
Great. talk soon.

11:33.876 --> 11:35.777
(telephone rings)

11:35.861 --> 11:37.629
(betty) i got james boyd
to do our shoot.

11:37.680 --> 11:39.964
And also, my dad's gonna
do our catering.
and i can get us

11:40.016 --> 11:42.450
The new york hall of science,
but only if i act fast.

11:42.535 --> 11:45.253
So i'm just gonna go aad
and book it, okay? bye.
no, wait, marc!

11:45.338 --> 11:47.672
But matt has a contact
at the planetarium.
i know, but--

11:47.740 --> 11:49.624
(telephone rings)
oh, hold on.
i have another call.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.643
Hey.
uh, i'm on the phone
with betty.

11:51.694 --> 11:54.412
Oh, good, so we can play that
game where we forget about her

11:54.480 --> 11:56.381
And see how long
she stays on?
(click)

11:56.448 --> 11:58.349
Okay, you may not be able
to see this

11:58.401 --> 12:00.335
Because you've got
your love-blinders on,

12:00.419 --> 12:02.553
But i don't think
we can count on matt.
what?

12:02.605 --> 12:04.956
Well, one, he's been showing up
late to y.e.t.i., and two,

12:05.024 --> 12:08.259
He spent last night watching
a man build a nest on youtube.

12:08.327 --> 12:10.228
We only have four days
to put this together,

12:10.295 --> 12:12.196
And we can't afford to have
anything bringing us down.

12:12.248 --> 12:13.982
Marc, that's ridic--
(telephone rings)

12:14.050 --> 12:16.985
Oh, hold on.
daniel meade's office.
hey.

12:17.069 --> 12:19.004
(click)
look, i know
he was acting

12:19.071 --> 12:21.940
A little weird last night,
but he is just as committed

12:22.007 --> 12:25.243
To this as we are.
okay, but the "fine dining
and autos" group

12:25.311 --> 12:30.382
Already had to kick out
one of their slackers.
what is that
supposed to mean?

12:30.433 --> 12:32.684
I'm saying it's a dog eat dog world
and matt's looking a lot like lunch.

12:36.504 --> 12:39.756
I don't know. i-i can't
decide on a ring.

12:39.823 --> 12:42.259
Molly's not one
for something showy,

12:42.310 --> 12:44.744
But i cat exactly get her
something cheap, right?

12:44.812 --> 12:48.198
I don't know. am i crazy
for even talking about this?

12:48.249 --> 12:50.500
As a mother,
i think so, yes.

12:50.551 --> 12:53.136
Seeing a son getting ready
to marry a dying woman--

12:53.204 --> 12:56.472
I just hate to see you
in that much pain.

12:56.524 --> 12:59.709
Come on, it's gonna be painful
whether we get married or not.

12:59.777 --> 13:02.245
If i can make one of molly's
biggest dreams come true,

13:02.296 --> 13:04.881
I-i can't think of anything
better than that.

13:07.101 --> 13:09.185
You're absolutely right.

13:11.772 --> 13:14.407
Whatever ups and downs
your father and i had,

13:14.492 --> 13:18.695
And we had
an awful lot of both...
(chuckles)

13:18.746 --> 13:22.949
I always loved him.

13:31.175 --> 13:34.778
When the time is right,
you give that to molly.

13:39.967 --> 13:42.552
(speaking indistinctly)

13:42.603 --> 13:44.537
I think
the time is right.

13:44.605 --> 13:46.072
(betty) daniel...

13:46.140 --> 13:49.058
What? why did he just
give me the--i hate the--

13:49.110 --> 13:51.127
You, too?
(door opens)

13:51.178 --> 13:55.131
(speaking indistinctly)

13:55.182 --> 13:57.634
Oh, my god, is he...

14:03.574 --> 14:05.725
(sighs)

14:05.810 --> 14:07.327
Oh.

14:08.863 --> 14:10.513
(laughs)

14:10.581 --> 14:14.584
(people cheering
and applauding)

14:14.635 --> 14:18.655
Oh, it's so romantic,
right?

14:18.706 --> 14:21.457
Now when molly
is all losing her hair,

14:21.509 --> 14:24.110
Daniel has no choice
but to stay by her side.

14:24.195 --> 14:25.729
Hilda.

14:25.796 --> 14:28.448
What? i wish i had somebody
who would love me

14:28.532 --> 14:30.517
