get out of your way.

17:14.229 --> 17:16.731
Bye!
wait, no, matt!

17:16.799 --> 17:17.949
No!

17:20.537 --> 17:21.970
Matt, don't go!

17:22.021 --> 17:24.306
What's going on?

17:24.374 --> 17:26.392
(sighs) i didn't know
how to tell you.

17:26.476 --> 17:29.445
I've been wanting to tell you
for a while now.

17:29.496 --> 17:32.414
It's been killing me.
but i just feel like...

17:32.465 --> 17:35.634
I'm losing my passion
for publishing.
what?

17:35.702 --> 17:37.987
I think i should
leave y.e.t.i.

17:38.054 --> 17:39.955
Wait,
hold on, what happened?

17:40.023 --> 17:42.824
You're really good at this,
and i thout you loved it.

17:42.876 --> 17:44.777
I did, i did.

17:44.861 --> 17:48.297
I've just been feeling...
drawn to something else.

17:48.365 --> 17:50.132
Oh.

17:50.183 --> 17:51.951
Uh, well, like what?

17:52.035 --> 17:54.870
Art.
art?

17:54.921 --> 17:57.306
Specifically, i-i want
to paint. oil paint.

17:57.357 --> 18:00.693
Oh, well, that's sort of
out of left field.

18:00.760 --> 18:03.078
Actually, i've always been
terested in painting.

18:03.129 --> 18:05.080
And i just
can't stop feeling

18:05.131 --> 18:07.883
That maybe i got on
the wrong path.

18:07.934 --> 18:10.286
There are some night classes
i want to take.

18:10.353 --> 18:12.921
They start next week.
are you freaked out?

18:12.973 --> 18:15.975
You seem freaked out.
no, no. no, i'm not.
i'm fine. it just--

18:16.059 --> 18:18.527
It's just a lot to process,
but, you know,

18:18.578 --> 18:20.996
If you're passionate
about art, then... great.

18:21.047 --> 18:23.148
I support you 100%.

18:23.233 --> 18:24.583
(chuckles softly)

18:24.668 --> 18:26.435
Wow.

18:26.486 --> 18:28.671
That is so nice to hear.

18:28.738 --> 18:32.040
My family doesn't t-tend
to see things the same way.

18:32.092 --> 18:34.393
So... we're okay?

18:34.477 --> 18:38.063
Yes, of course we're okay.

18:38.131 --> 18:40.866
(betty) it's just
a little bit confusing.

18:40.934 --> 18:42.935
(daniel) publishing can't be
the only thing

18:43.019 --> 18:46.388
You like about him.
no, of course not.
i mean, he's sweet and--

18:46.456 --> 18:48.991
And goofy, and his bad jokes
make me laugh.

18:49.042 --> 18:51.460
And things are just better
when he's there.

18:51.511 --> 18:53.645
Yeah, well,
none of that's changed.

18:53.730 --> 18:56.281
Even though he doesn't do
the same thing as you,

18:56.366 --> 19:00.252
He's still the guy you
fell in love with, right?
wow, you've gotten all wise
since you've been engaged.

19:00.320 --> 19:02.721
(laughs) yeah.
kinda weird, right?

19:02.806 --> 19:05.691
The new york hall of science
is now saying no,

19:05.775 --> 19:07.710
And judging
by the restraining order

19:07.777 --> 19:10.462
They sent me this morning,
they mean it.
well, what are we
gonna do?

19:10.547 --> 19:13.465
(sighs)
we can't just paint stars
in your apartment

19:13.550 --> 19:15.284
And call it the planetarium.

19:15.335 --> 19:17.452
I mean, this is adele,
not amy winehouse.
(cell phone rings)

19:17.504 --> 19:20.723
Wow, betty,
that was really funny.
thank you. betty suarez.

19:20.774 --> 19:23.359
We're never
gonna be editors.
yeah, of course
i can be there today.

19:23.410 --> 19:26.729
I'm gonna go
kill myself now.
thank you.
we got the planetaum!

19:26.796 --> 19:29.498
Oh, my god,
that is great!
i just have to go down
and sign the contract.

19:29.566 --> 19:33.034
Okayi'll--
i'll go with you
(wilhelmina)
are you out of your mind?!

19:33.086 --> 19:35.187
Maybe not.
go. go, go.

19:35.271 --> 19:37.823
(wilhelmina) oh, her bust
looks nonexistent.

19:37.891 --> 19:39.375
For god sake, claire,

19:39.442 --> 19:42.511
Put your bifocals on.
she looks hideous.
how insensitive of me.

19:42.562 --> 19:44.746
The love of your life
stole all your money

19:44.798 --> 19:48.083
And fled the continent
just to get away from you.

19:48.134 --> 19:51.553
