(click)

23:18.092 --> 23:19.793
Why are you
showing me these?

23:19.844 --> 23:22.145
Well, it does seem odd, given
th i don't care for you,

23:22.230 --> 23:24.448
But in this case,
your plucky immigrant zeal

23:24.532 --> 23:26.433
Could be a good thing.

23:26.500 --> 23:28.301
I want matt back
in y.e.t.i.

23:28.369 --> 23:31.621
Well, he's pretty passionate
about art now.

23:31.706 --> 23:34.240
He always starts
that way.

23:34.292 --> 23:37.511
I don't want matt to be one
of those incredibly rich men

23:38.312 --> 23:40.213
Who never accomplish
anything.

23:40.280 --> 23:42.832
I think if he finishes
this program,

23:42.900 --> 23:44.850
He'll stick with publishing.

23:44.935 --> 23:47.036
Of course,
i can't tell him that.

23:47.104 --> 23:50.506
It has to come
from you.

23:50.574 --> 23:52.108
Uh, mrs. hartley,

23:52.159 --> 23:55.211
I-i really don't feel
comfortable doing that.

23:55.278 --> 23:57.513
I understand.

23:57.581 --> 24:00.349
Well,
enjoy the planetarium.

24:00.400 --> 24:02.985
I know how important
this project is for you

24:03.036 --> 24:04.554
And your career.

24:06.605 --> 24:09.974
It'd be such a shame
if anything went wrong.

24:13.161 --> 24:15.095
